<br>
1)  People under 60 have a difficult time getting groups on Stormhammer because 90% of the server (not counting Alts) is level 60 or over.<br>
<br>
2)  There is always a supply of medium to high end items for sale in the bazaar (even if they may be outrageously priced at times).  You can always buy Boots of Flowing Slime (60-70K), Mithril Gauntlets (120K), Mithril Boots (120K), Fungi Tunic (70K), Blade of Carnage (300k), Skyshine MQs (15k-100K depending on the piece), Wand of the War Wizard (120K), etc.<br>
<br>
3)  There are 10+ guilds that could handle Statue or above content on a good day.<br>
<br>
I have always believed that things were the same on Stormhammer as on Vazaelle.  However, now I am wondering if I have lost touch with reality. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caenyien>Caenyien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/25/02 2:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1793.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reality.</span><hr size=1> <br>
